        Bob Ross, holding a palette in left hand and a two inch brush in his right hand standing in his studio.</p>
   </div> 
     <div id="tribute-info">
   <ul>
    <li>Robert Norman Ross born <strong>October 29, 1942</strong></li>
   <li>In <strong>1961, 18-year-old Ross</strong> enlisted in the United States Air Force, of service for 20 years.
   During his 20-year Air Force career, Ross developed an interest in painting after attending an art class at the Anchorage U.S.O. club.</li>
   <li>Eventually, Ross's income from sales surpassed his military salary. He retired from the Air Force in 1981 as a master sergeant</li>
   <li>Ross was noted for his permed hair, which he ultimately disliked but kept after he had integrated it into the company logo.</li>
   <li>The show "The joy of painting" ran from <strong>January 11, 1983, to May 17, 1994</strong></li>
   <li>Ross used a wet-on-wet oil painting technique of painting over a thin base layer of wet paint.</li>
   <li>Ross painted an estimated <strong>30,000</strong> paintings during his lifetime.</li>
   <li>Bob Ross Died on <strong>July 4, 1995 (aged 52)</strong></li>
 </ul>
